As for my druid aversion, well I was about over it.  As I said earlier, I like having a druid in the group, at least one who knows what role to assume given group makeup, and most do at this point.  <br>
<br>
But a month or two ago, I had this urge to go see what this &quot;frenzy&quot; camp in Lguk was all about.  I had heard bout people soloing it, mostly necros, and wanted to see if I could solo it too!  Oh, and get an FBSS to use for twinkage.  So I make up a batch of ITU potions, use one, and head down.  I get there, meet my friend who is a wizard and was holding the camp, and we kill a couple of spawns.  Then all of a sudden this assling druid runs into the camp trailing (and i shit you not) about 20 undead frogs!  Gah!  He goes LD immediately and the frogs all jump on me.  I don't know the way out, got 20 frogs on me, and my partner just gated.  I die and have to call in a favor to get myself rezzed and the exp back.  I talked to Cretain who was friends with this dr00d and he told me the drood was pissed that I was camping it cause he wanted to camp it.  Good reason huh? <br>
<br>
Anyhow, I've been trained, KSed, quadkited over and killed, mocked, and loot screwed by members of your class.  Forgive me if I seem a bit down on the druid class, it's a knee jerk reaction.  Lately I've been trying to come back to neutral again, and am doing much better.  I think the arena therapy has been helping with that.  I don't feel quite so bitter after I've killed 10 or so . . . lemme see, last person who actually beat me was a lvl 60 warrior, and I was 53 at the time.  Man warriors can be real badasses at PvP, it's amazing.  Even now I have serious trouble vs. them.  All casting classes are easy tho, druids being the strongest of them.  <br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
<br>
Lan<br>
<br>
