<br>
We try so hard to show others our generosity and integrity, we deal with the snide comments, stereotypes, and being called dr00ds, and then some dinkus comes and pulls a stunt like this, or like what happened to Land in Guk, and we are back where we started.   I am too far removed from the occurances to even attempt commentary on the events with Ghon.  With the information given, I can see both sides of the coin; that he genuinely thought he was responsible for the fish's spawn, and also that he was being slimey and premeditative in his kill steal.  I wasn't there, I wasn't in his head, and I sure don't know what he was thinking, so I shan't venture an opinion either way.  I DO however know Shurakair, and there are not enough amiable expressions in the language to do him justice.  He gives selflessly, is quick to help, and slow to criticise.  A better example of a druid you shall not find..period.<br>
<br>
Landragoran, I have met you before, a long time ago.  You are a very nice guy yourself, and I am very sorry you have had less than favourable experiences in your past with druids.  On behalf of my class, I apologise.  How very sad that such events have occured to make you believe that people aren't inherently good, though this is a completely different subject I care not to broach. =)  Do however, be careful in the construction of your arguement.  I too read your initial post as a debasement first of Shurakair's abilities, and then of druids in general, though I do not believe that was your intention.  <br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
